dc_title_s: LiDAR-Derived Countywide 1-ft Bare Earth DEM (ft) for Trempealeau County, WI 2022
dc_description_s: This data represents a LiDAR-derived 1-ft Bare Earth Digital Elevation Model (DEM) for Trempealeau County, Wisconsin in 2022. This dataset has elevation values in feet and is in the WISCRS coordinate system for Trempealeau County, WI. A DEM represents the bare-Earth surface, removing all natural and built features.
dc_creator_sm: Wisconsin Department of Administration - Geographic Information Office
uw_supplemental_s: This lidar data dataset was created by the WisconsinView Partners (WVP) – the WI Department of Administration’s Geographic Information Office in collaboration with the UW-Madison WisconsinView repository. Original lidar data in tiled format from federal or local county/city lidar projects were used to create countywide mosaics of datasets such as DEMS, Intensity images, and DSMs in various projections and coordinate systems. For original vendor XML metadata please visit: https://web.s3.wisc.edu/wsco-wisconsinview/lidar/Trempealeau/Trempealeau_2022_3DEP_Delivery/Metadata/Metadata.zip
